	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I notice there are a lot of spiraling explosion where animated explosion sprites get activated one after another while rotate their spawning direction.
<br />
<br />However they might be using a trick where the spiraling explosions are actually prerendered overlayed sprites.  There might be 24x24 pixels of sprites that look like 5 individual overlapping 16x16 explosion sprites.
<br />
<br />That could make it appear like the NES is doing more sprites than it really is.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


